<item>
            <title>[WICKET-4501] NumberTextField&lt;BigDecimal&gt; renders its value in unsupported number format </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4501</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The issue is similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-3591&quot; title=&quot;NumberTextField and RangeTextField should always render/parse its value with English locale&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-3591&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-3591&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; but its fix doesn&apos;t help when the model object of the NumberTextField is a BigDecimal because BigDecimalConverter#convertToString() produces something like &quot;123, 456, 789&quot; and this is not supported by &amp;lt;input type=&quot;number&quot;&amp;gt;&apos;s spec: &lt;a href=&quot;http://dev.w3.org/html5/markup/datatypes.html#common.data.float&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://dev.w3.org/html5/markup/datatypes.html#common.data.float&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
